Reflecting on the Write Your Way to Freedom Annual Event - a highlight of 2022 for me 🥰🥰

It was such a beautiful weekend, and I had the best time creating this video.

(It’s funny how many things you can get done when you’re sick and have to skip out on meetings for a few days!) 😅

If you were there, here’s your chance to relive the wonderful time we had. If you weren’t, here’s just a peek into what you have to look forward to next year. 😉

Our annual live event, *open to all students,* is a time for us to get together irl, reflect on our businesses, and get inspiration on ways we can all reach our next levels.

It’s a weekend full of… 

❤️ Mindset exercises 
🏖️ Beach lunches
😍 Connection with new friends
😂 And, of course, some copywriting chat

I absolutely cannot wait to see you all again next year—and hopefully see some new faces, too! 🥰

Coming in 2023…

Felt like this deserved a permanent home on the grid.

I always knew I’d write books, but I thought I’d wait until I was older and wiser. 

Ya know, writing them from a cabin in the woods, wearing flowy dresses, and smart tortoise shell glasses, lol

But two years ago I realized that it was just an excuse because really I was scared shitless.

The week I signed with my publisher I’d periodically cringe from the fear I had around putting something out into the world that wasn’t digital - it couldn’t ever be deleted or even reworded in the middle of a sleepless night. 

Literally cringed. Ben caught me a few times and asked if I was ok. 😂

I was watching an interview with Billie Ellish, where she was encouraging David Letterman to sing so they could make a little song together. He stopped and said, “this is so embarrassing” obviously referring to trying to sing in front of her and her brother. But a knowing look crossed her face and she replied, “oh, I’m always embarrassed when I’m making music.”

I laughed. 

Isn’t this the story we continue to hear? 

Do it scared. 
Do it when it makes you cringe a bit. 
It’s really as simple as that.

So on the grid she goes. 
Coming out from the stories. 
The love y’all shared in my dms yesterday meant so much to me 🥰 thank you.

✨Bennett’s Birth Story✨

Most of my life I thought I'd never have kids. The initial shift came from an unexpected conversation with a quirky baker I met in Panama.

When I told him I had zero desire to give birth, he shared he was sad he’d never get to have that experience. I told him he was crazy.

The next day, he handed me a copy of Spiritual Midwifery (meaning he was backpacking through Central America lugging it around)

My mind didn't change overnight, but it was the beginning of a decade long shift. A lot of things had to fall into place for me to feel ready to meet Bennett.

His birth was quite the journey. Beginning with my water breaking, 36 hours at home, then moving to the hospital where he joined us after 60 hours and 10 minutes in total.

Since I’ve had some fairly traumatic hospital experiences, my plan was to give birth at home. In a birth class I shared what I feared most was a hospital transfer. I was scared I would panic. But after a series of events we decided to head to the hospital. Ultimately, it was an empowering decision.

My favorite part of labor was pushing. Ben showed me a breathing technique he used for lifting. But every time someone asked him a question and I was left to breathe alone, I lost my rhythm. So he stayed face to face with me for 2 hours coaching me through.

I was curious about how I’d feel at the end of labor. Would I be scared? Would I not want to go through that again?

But I looked at Ben about an hour after Bennett was born and said in my delirium, “I could do that again.” He laughed and said, “I know you could.”

Bennett’s birth was empowering in completely unexpected ways. Including the healing I experienced around having a positive hospital experience.

If you’re pregnant or thinking about being pregnant, one of the most important things you can do is protect your mind. So I want to add while my birth story isn’t pretty, I don’t think it was traumatic 🙏 we all have depths of untapped strength and labor is renowned for revealing this.

You can hear the full story by clicking “Latest Podcast Episode" in my bio.

📸 by my incredible doula @rebeccacoursey_photosandfilm - couldn't have done it without her 💞

Trying to find the work + life balance that feels right for this season of life 🍃

On Mother’s Day, Ben asked me how I was feeling and without really thinking I replied, “I’m having a hard time connecting with how I’m feeling because I’m just thinking about you and Bennett.” We made eye contact and laughed 😂

While that sounds about right, I’m not really interested in a martyrdom motherhood. I’m definitely taking steps to reconnect with myself but I’m not in any rush to make it happen.

Right now is super snuggly and I’m enjoying this sweet baby boy so much.

I’m sure I’ll get more solid footing because it’s already happening naturally but what I know so far is I want my days to be a hybrid of work and stay at home mom life. And I want more of the latter than I ever would have guessed.

I also hate pumping (bc of D-MER) but love breastfeeding, so I’m trying to make space in my days for more. Scheduling meetings around feedings is doing the trick 🙌 sometimes even breastfeeding on calls when Bennett needs to.

Just over here soaking it all in and figuring it out as I go.

🎉 Our business has made it onto the Inc 5000 list this year! 🎉

To top it all off, we’ve ranked #24 in education, and #1256 overall. 😍

It’s truly our students’ success that’s made this possible. 👏

I remember when it was just me, our COO Sarah Siegfried, and well under 100 students back in 2018. 

Now we have… 

🎊 Over 5,700 students working towards lives of freedom
🎊 A team of 21 people helping me support them
🎊 The 5 year anniversary of Write Your Way to Freedom coming up in October 👏 

Write Your Way to Freedom students have used the program in so many different ways to make it work for their specific goals. 

Their amazing work and the way they all support each other is what makes it the program it is today.

And there’s evidence of this on a daily basis…

🎉 In our Wednesday Wins where we celebrate each step of the journey
🎉 In the updates and encouragement students share in discussions
🎉 In the student success stories that highlight achievements

It’s truly getting difficult to keep up with the incredible accomplishments of our students! 🥳

And I’m in awe of the amazing companies they’re working with. Here are **just a few.**

💫 Fenty

We’ve already been a well-known name in the industry for a few years now, and the recognition of being on Inc 5000 strengthens what it means to be a Write Your Way to Freedom student even more. 

I’m so excited to see what the future holds for us. 🥳

Spending the next three weeks teaching copywriting to the biggest name in the game 😎✌️

When you get your online community together in real life, you get an opportunity to ✨feel✨ the impact of good marketing.

Good marketing often goes unnoticed because it’s not flagged as cringy or salesy by our minds.

Truly good marketing is world building. 

It brings people together under the banner of a common mission.

And that is truly magical ✨

I love these people so much. I’m so grateful for how my lil’ ol’ online course has transformed over the last 5 years into a movement with the most amazing people.

Strangers on the internet who’ve become some of my closest and dearest friends.

What a time to be alive.
Every day?? 🤣🤣🤣

I just never want to forget this moment. 
That is all.
So insanely proud of my team and the work that we do 🥹 every day is truly a dream come true.

Every few days I look at Ben and say “this is my favorite age.” 

It’s all so fun and I just love him so much. There’s so many little things I never want to forget. Like his distinct giggle when I hold him face to face from his hips. How he leans over to look at Ben across the room. How he coos to get my attention. 

Thank you @kinder.studio.photography for these. So grateful to have captured this time. 🥰
